Sec. 55.001.

POWERS.

An association formed under this chapter

may:
(1) borrow money for and lend money to its members;
(2) discount, rediscount, endorse, purchase, or sell notes,
bills, or other evidences of indebtedness of its members that may be
discounted or rediscounted under the rules prescribed by the Farm
Credit Administration; and
(3) exercise the powers authorized by the general
corporation laws of this state unless the law granting the power
conflicts with this chapter.
Acts 1981, 67th Leg., p. 1121, ch. 388, Sec. 1, eff. Sept. 1, 1981.

